featuresTraits:
Hobbit Resilience: Advantage on saving throws against being frightened.
Hobbit Nimbleness: Can move through the space of any creature larger than yours.
Brave Little Souls: Once per long rest, reroll a failed attack, check, or save.

--- CALLING: Gardener (Shire Sage) ---
Keepers of the green and growing things, Gardeners understand the secret language of plants and the subtle ways of the wilder parts of the Shire.

--- Learned Calling Abilities ---
- Soothing Poultice: Once per short rest, as an action, you can apply a poultice to a creature. They regain 1d4 + your Spirit modifier in Fortitude. This increases to 1d6 at level 5.
- Goodberry Wine: Once per long rest, you can spend 10 minutes brewing a small batch of Goodberry Wine. One creature who drinks it gains advantage on their next saving throw against poison or disease within 1 hour.
ideals: Comfort and friendship are the best things in life.
bonds: My home and my garden mean everything to me.
flaws: Perhaps a bit too fond of second breakfast.
appearanceNotes: Rosy cheeks and a friendly smile.
